      {
        "id": 2227813,
        "name": "Jay S. Miller",
        "username": "Jay_S_Miller",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/ea5d25/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2017-07-27T19:33:27.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I bought 10 cases of 1981s as futures (Las Cases, Ducru, La Mission, et al) and was pleased with the purchase. Drank them over a 20-25 year period but I suspect that they would still be in good shape today. If you see them at auction, they\u2019re a good gamble.<br>\nRe Tempier Rose, I\u2019ve felt that they are best with 1-2 years of bottle age. I recently discovered a few bottles of 2009 hiding in the cellar. They were fine but lacking the vibrancy of youth.<br>\nDoctorJay</p>",
